{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is summary-write logic + findings read from persistence for the same round (module handoff/state consistency), not just one pure function. Real OS/network/subprocess is not required; a local DB/repo fixture is enough. No LLM output dependence.","test_description":"Seed stored findings for round R with at least one FAIL, attempt to persist a PASS summary for round R through the real service/repository wiring, and assert write is rejected with a clear validation error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Bug appears at boundary between gate computation and stored findings source-of-truth. Need wired modules to prove gate ignores conflicting manual text. No real OS/network/process needed; no model-output dependence.","test_description":"Persist findings containing FAIL plus a conflicting manual summary text claiming PASS, run stop-gate computation via service stack, and assert verdict is non-PASS based on stored findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Requires coordination of input handling/authorization with audit logging persistence. A unit test of flag parsing alone would miss missing-audit or logging-handoff failures. No real