nt":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.56,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Decision uses stored results + rounds-remaining state; failure is orchestration/state logic across modules, not model-quality. No real OS/network/process required, and unresolved MUST-FIX can be fixture data. Rejected Agentic because behavior text bases decision on stored results, not correctness of new model output.","test_description":"Seed state with rounds_exhausted=true and stored unresolved MUST-FIX findings, execute gate decision path, and assert escalation outcome plus PASS denial.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This explicitly requires a live multi-round agent pipeline with sequential rounds and terminal escalation behavior; minimum failure boundary is cross-step workflow state progression, not a single call. Includes LLM-involved stages across rounds, so lower Integration would miss sequencing/handoff failures.","test_description":"Execute a real multi-round review workflow on an updated diff where MUST-FIX remains unresolved through final allowed round; assert final state blocks PASS and emits escalation record/notification.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.24,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
